div1.p: IN THE CIRCUIT COURT FOR THE NINTH CIRCUIT, WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF L.J. URANN FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.} WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.
The United States of America, 9th Circuit, Western District of Washington, ss.
To L.C. Smith, Sheriff of King County, Washington and Morris Wolf, Agent of the State of Massachusetts:

We command you that the body of L.H. Urann; in your custody detained, as it is said, together with the day and cause of his caption and detention, you safely have before Hon. C.H. Hanford, judge of our circuit court of the United States, within and for the on the 30d day of July, 1905, at the hour of 10:00 a.m., district aforesaid, to do and receive all and singular those things which the said Hon. C.H. Hanford, judge of our said circuit court, shall thenaand there consider of him in this behalf; and have you then and there this writ.
Witness the Hon. MELVILLE W. FULLER, Chief Justice of the United States, and the seal of the said Circuit Court, the 1st day of July, 1905.
In the United States Circuit Court FOR THE Western District of Washington NORTHERN DIVISION
In the Matter of the Petition of L.J. Urann for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
FILED IN THE U.S. Circuit Court, Western Dist. of Washington. Jul 3, 1905 A. REEVES AYRES, Clerk HM Matthew, Dep.

Service of papers, except in process, in this cause may be made upon GRAY&BURNAMVince H. Faben Vince H. Faben Attorneys for Petitioner 50Z-8-10 MUTUAL LIFE BUILDING PHONES, SUNSET MAIN 1302, IND. A 1844 SEATTLE, WASH.
